"""
Body Mesh v6 — accurate shape + hole-free interior
====================================================
TWO MASKS PER REGION (the key architectural fix):

  edge mask     = actual seg pixels sliced to zone
                  → correct shape outline (follows shirt curves, armhole notch)
                  → used for: Delaunay contour points, draw_layer outline

  interior mask = solid row-fill of edge mask
                  → spans left-to-right between outermost seg pixels per row
                  → bridges arm/hand gaps so Delaunay grid has no holes
                  → used for: Delaunay interior grid point test only

Previously the solid fill was used for BOTH outline AND interior,
causing the mesh to draw a rectangular boundary instead of the shirt shape,
making it spill outside the actual garment.

Waistband: full-width median saturation scan, largest gradient = shirt/pants boundary.
Works at all rotation angles (old single-column scan failed at side view).

Run:  streamlit run app.py
"""

